# Admin Dashboard - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Next.js 14 (App Router) internal admin dashboard for Facebook operations.
TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui components, TanStack Query.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14.1.0 with App Router
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui component library
- TanStack Query (React Query) for server state
- NextAuth.js for authentication
- Recharts for data visualization
- Zod for validation, React Hook Form for forms
- Vitest + Testing Library for tests

## Directory Structure
- `src/app/` - Next.js App Router pages
  - `page.tsx` - Dashboard home
  - `login/` - Auth pages
  - `users/` - User management
  - `moderation/` - Content moderation queue
  - `ads/` - Ad review
  - `analytics/` - Analytics dashboard
  - `system/` - System health
  - `audit/` - Audit logs
  - `settings/` - Admin settings
- `src/components/`
  - `ui/` - Base shadcn/ui components (DO NOT modify directly)
  - `common/` - Shared components (data-table, search, pagination)
  - `layout/` - Sidebar, header, breadcrumb
  - `{feature}/` - Feature-specific components
- `src/lib/api/` - API service layer (axios-based)
- `src/hooks/` - TanStack Query hooks
- `src/types/` - TypeScript type definitions
- `src/providers/` - React context providers
- `src/middleware.ts` - Auth + RBAC route protection

## Commands
- Dev: `npm run dev` (port 3000)
- Build: `npm run build`
- Test: `npx vitest`
- Lint: `npm run lint`
- Type check: `npx tsc --noEmit`

## Component Patterns
- Server Components by default, add 'use client' only when needed
- Use TanStack Query for ALL server state (never useState for API data)
- Use shadcn/ui primitives from src/components/ui/
- Use CVA (class-variance-authority) for component variants
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod resolver

## Role-Based Access
- Routes are protected by middleware.ts
- Roles: super_admin, content_moderator, ad_reviewer, analyst
- Check role before rendering admin-only actions

## Do NOT
- Do not modify src/components/ui/ files (they are shadcn/ui generated)
- Do not use default exports (use named exports only)
- Do not use `any` type
- Do not fetch data in components (use hooks from src/hooks/)
- Do not add tailwind classes that conflict with shadcn/ui theme
- Do not hardcode API URLs (use src/lib/api/client.ts)
